rom Ukraine to the parishes of the Manitoba prairie. In a detailed examination of the exteriors and interiors of forty-nine churches, the book establishes a typology of Ukrainian church designs. Biographies of the architects, master builders, and artists are included, along with a guide to the art and architecture of a Ukrainian church.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitecture religieusexInfluence ukrainiennexManitoba. 0aArchitecture religieusexManitoba. 0aArchitecture religieusexUkraine. 0aCatholic church buildingsxManitoba. 0aCatholic church buildingszManitoba. 0aChurch architecturexUkraine. 0aChurch architecturexUkrainian influencesxManitoba. 0aChurch architecturezManitobaxUkrainian influences. 0aChurch architecturezUkraine. 0aOrthodox Eastern church buildingsxManitoba. 0aOrthodox Eastern church buildingszManitoba. 0aÉglises orthodoxes (Édifices)xManitobaxManitobaxUkraine. 7aARCHITECTURE / Buildings / Religious.2bisacsh1 aHryniuk, Stella, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aYereniuk, Roman, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088755345540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780887553455423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780887553455/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles